<FIRST>r i PM-Philippines-Escape     05-30 0176</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Philippines-Escape,0183</SECOND>
<HEAD>10 Inmates Kill Two Prison Guards In Escape</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ten prisoners facing charges
including murder, rape and auto theft killed two guards in a
provincial jail today, looted the prison's armory and escaped,
police reported.
   Police said escape took place at the Pampanga jail in the town
of San Fernando, about 30 miles north of Manila.
   The escapees were led by two trusties who clubbed and stabbed to
death two guards in their sleep, said Sgt. Ronnie Cunanan, a police
investigator.
   Cunanan said the two trusties, who were both awaiting trial for
murder, then took the prison keys from one guard's body and
unlocked all the jail's cells, where about 100 prisoners were held.
They then took five revolvers and four shotguns from the prison's
armory.
   The escapees also beat up a prison guard trainee before fleeing.
   Cunanan said only eight other prisoners joined the escape, while
the rest waited for police, who arrived at the jail more than four
hours later.
   Authorities have launched a manhunt for the escapees.
</TEXT>
