<HEAD>U.S. Jet Fighter Makes Emergency Landing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A U.S. Air Force F-16 jet fighter made an emergency
landing at an airport in northern Japan after the pilot noticed a
drop in the engine's hydraulic pressure, a government official said
today.
   Jeff Conners was flying the jet, which landed safely Monday at
Akita Airport, about 280 miles north of Tokyo, a Transport Ministry
official said.
   He said Conners was conducting routine training with three other
F-16s belonging to the 13th Tactical Fighter Squadron based at
Misawa, northern Japan, when he asked permission from local
aviation authorities to land at the civilian airport.
