<SECOND>PM-Marine Drowns,0162</SECOND>
<HEAD>U.S. Marine Drowns in Pool at American Embassy</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KUWAIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A U.S. Marine assigned to the American Embassy in
Kuwait drowned in the embassy swimming pool after he hit his head
while swimming, an embassy spokesman said today.
   ``The sailor ... apparently struck his head on the side of the
pool and lost consciousness. He was discovered on the bottom of the
pool,'' said the spokesman, who could not be identified under
embassy rules.
   The incident occurred Thursday.
   The Marine was pronounced dead on arrival at Amir Hospital,
Kuwait's main medical facility, said the spokesman. He said the
Marine's name was being withheld pending notification of his family.
   The Kuwaiti daily newspaper al-Watan reported that the Marine
was thrown into the pool by a group of colleagues during a
children's party at the embassy.
   Al-Watan said other Marines were called back to the pool by a
child who said the man could not swim.
