<HEAD>U.S. Navy Man Killed in Car Accident</HEAD>
<HEAD>EDS: Retransmitting a0535 to CORRECT cycle designator.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A U.S. Navy man was killed today when his
motorcycle was hit by a car, police said.
   A local police officer, who spoke on condition of anonymity,
identifed the victim as Petty Officer 1st Class William A.
Phillips, 36, a crewman of the U.S. aircraft carrier Midway. His
hometown was not available from Japanese police or U.S. military
spokesmen.
   Phillips was on his way to the U.S. Navy base at Yokosuka, about
30 miles southwest of Tokyo, when a car drove out of a parking lot
and crashed into him, the officer said.
   The driver of the car, Hideyuki Tanaka, 21, was arrested on
charges of negligence resulting in death, the officer said.
