<HEAD>Seven Reported Shot During Holdup Attempt</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: UPDATES throughhout to quotes, details from bank official.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bungled armored truck holdup at a Wells
Fargo Bank branch today ended in a shootout that left seven people,
including five bank customers, wounded, officials said.
   The victims included a guard, five customers and the alleged
gunman; at least one of whom was reported in critical condition,
said fire department Inspector Ed Reed.
   ``One of the armored car service guards was taking a service
delivery back to his truck. There was an exchange of gunfire. The
guard was shot first,'' said Wes Lockwood, assistant vice president
of public relations for Wells Fargo.
   The bank had opened as usual at 9 a.m., he said, but closed
after the shooting so investigators could question employees and
witnesses.
