<HEAD>U.S. Condemns Attacks by Israeli Vigilantes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The U.S. government on Tuesday denounced
vigilante attacks by Jewish settlers in the Israel-occupied West
Bank.
   ``We urge all sides to refrain from actions that contribute to
raising the level of violence and hinder efforts to establish a
dialogue between Israelis and Palestinians,'' State Department
spokesman Richard Boucher told reporters.
   Boucher didn't go into detail, but his comment came after what
the Israeli media called one of the worst vigilante attacks of the
nearly 18-month Palestinian uprising.
