the Israeli government's views that there could be `no
justification for people taking the law into their own hands.' We
certainly agree with that.''
   A 13-year-old girl became the 500th Palestinian killed in the
uprising in the incident Monday, when about two-dozen Jewish
settlers set a wheat field and part of a house ablaze in the
farming village of Kifil Harith.
   They also smashed windows in a car and a truck and shot up
several rooftop water tanks. The girl, Ibtisam Bozieh, was struck
in the chest by a bullet fired through a shutter, her family said.
