<HEAD>Rain Improves Crop Conditions</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rain has improved crop conditions in the
central United States, Northern Plains and into the East, with
thunderstorms expected in the central region during the next few
days, the Agriculture Department drought task force said Tuesday.
   The overall outlook is very good for the next 10 days, task
force said.
   The rain on pastures and ranges in the central part of the
country is expected to slow the number of cows being slaughtered.
