<FIRST>r a AM-BridgeCollapse     05-30 0184</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Bridge Collapse,0191</SECOND>
<HEAD>First Body Recovered Near Collapsed Bridge</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CINCINNATI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman's body was pulled Tuesday from the
Great Miami River in the first recovery of a victim from the bridge
collapse last week that dropped at least two vehicles into the
rain-swollen river.
   Four people are still missing, officials believe.
   Recovery teams using sonar detected what appeared to be two
vehicles resting on the river's bottom near the bridge. The current
was too strong to allow divers into the water.
   ``We probably won't send the divers in until Thursday,'' said
Hamilton County Sheriff Simon Leis Jr..
   The woman's body was found about five miles downstream from the
bridge, snagged in debris about 40 feet from shore, said Hamilton
County sheriff's Col. Ray Hoffbauer.
   Authorities did not release her name.
   A 100-foot section of the one-lane bridge collapsed Friday about
seven miles northwest of Cincinnati.
   The bridge opened Dec. 15 to temporarily replace a 94-year-old
bridge being rebuilt a few feet away. Officials said river currents
and pounding from debris probably caused the collapse.
   The National Transportation Safety Board is investigating.
