<HEAD>Pemex Forms International Affilate for Exporting Crude Oils</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEXICO CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The government oil monopoly Pemex has formed
a new international affiliate for the export of crude oils
worldwide, the company announced.
   In a statement released in Mexico City Monday, Pemex said the
new affiliate will be known as PMI Comercio Internacional, S.A. de
C.V. and will ``be charged with bringing to the world market
Mexican petroleum products ... with the goal of being more
competitive and agile.''
   The statement said the announcement was initially made in Tokyo
by company director Francisco Rojas, who is in Japan to renegotiate
a 10-year contract to continue exporting Mexican petroleum to the
Asian nation.
   Pemex exports oil to Japan through the Mexican Petroleum
Importing Co., a partnership of Pemex and Japanese industrialists.
