trading today, buoyed mainly by the dollar's strength in foreign
exchange.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials rose 4.02 points to
2,497.79.
   In the broader market, about eight stocks rose for every five
that fell on the New York Stock Exchange, with 524 up, 322 down and
493 unchanged.
   Volume on the Big Board came to 23.73 million shares.
   ``It's the strength of the dollar again that's propelling the
market,'' said Hildegarde Zagorski, a stock analyst with
Prudential-Bache Securities Inc.
   A firmer dollar helps attract foreign money to stocks, bonds and
other investment products.
   Analysts said stocks were also helped by a drop in interest
rates in the credit markets and prospects that the Federal Reserve
will ease its credit policies to control the dollar.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks rose
