<FILEID>AP-NR-05-30-89 1115EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f BC-Britain-Gateway     05-30 0309</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Britain-Gateway,0319</SECOND>
<HEAD>Isosceles Consortium Raises Offer For Gateway</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Isosceles PLC, a consortium of dissatisfied
British institutional shareholders in Gateway Corp. PLC, on Tuesday
raised its hostile bid for the British food retailer to 1.87
billion pounds ($2.9 billion).
   Gateway holders can choose between 210 pence ($3.30) in cash per
share or 195 pence ($3.06) in cash, plus at least 15 pence (24
cents) worth of stock in Isosceles.
   The new offer compares with the original cash offer of 1.7
billion pounds ($2.7 billion), or 195 pence ($3.06) per share,
which was launched on April 18.
   Isosceles, a company formed specifically to make the bid for
Gateway, said the new offer wouldn't be increased unless another
bidder for Gateway emerged.
   Gateway shares rose on the announcement, gaining 7.5 pence (12
cents) to 204.5 pence ($3.21) by midafternoon on London's Stock
Exchange. The shares had been trading above 195 pence ($3.06) in
recent trading sessions in anticipation of a higher bid.
   Isosceles is seeking to split Gateway by selling its non-food
interests and its larger stores. The consortium already has a firm
agreement to sell 62 of the larger stores to Asda Group PLC,
another British retailer, for 702 million pounds ($1.1 billion).
   The remaining Gateway interests would then be privately held by
the Isosceles consortium, which aims to float its shares on the
London Stock Exchange within the next three to five years.
   As a result, the Isosceles stock offered under the revised bid
would be unlisted, though the consortium said the shares would be
``freely transferable.''
   Isosceles said the revised offer could involve the issue of as
much as 52 percent of Isosceles' share capital. In addition, if the
bid succeeds, Isosceles plans to issue as much as 15 percent of its
stock to Gateway managers as part of a scheme of share option
incentives.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
