<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Private exporters say China has purchased
200,000 metric tons of soft red winter wheat for delivery this
market year, the Department of Agriculture reported Tuesday.
   The market year begins Thursday.
   Exporters are required by law to inform the USDA within one
business day of any purchase of 100,000 metric tons or more of any
single commodity by a single buyer.
