<SECOND>BC-Wickes Sale,0153</SECOND>
<HEAD>Furniture, Hardware Division Sales Completed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTA MONICA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Wickes Cos. Inc. completed the
previously announced sales of its Wickes Furniture and Orchard
Supply hardware divisions for about $290 million, the company said
Tuesday.
   Orchard Supply, based in San Jose, was sold to a management-led
investor group headed by Maynard Jenkins, president and chief
executive officer of the hardware company. Wickes has previously
said the 31-store chain would be sold for $134 million.
   Wickes Furniture, based in Wheeling, Ill., was sold to a group
organized by its president and chief executive officer, John Klein.
The furniture company, which has 23 retail stores in Chicago, Los
Angeles, Minneapolis, Pittsburgh and Dallas, sold for $155 million,
the company said.
   Wickes, a conglomerate with holdings in retailing, auto products
and fabric and wallcoverings, has been selling assets since it was
bought last year by a partnership of Blackstone Capital Partners
and Wasserstein, Perella Partners.
</TEXT>
